21. Virtute, existimatione, nobilitate. The first of these words denotes ‘high principle' and its effect ‘probity’-—the second, ‘the reputation enjoyed by an individual among his fellow—men ’—-the third, simply ‘high birth’ or ‘a high social position.' A man might have ⁸ Virtus’ and yet not enjoy ⁴ Existimatio,’ and viee versa; a man might have both without being ‘ nobilis: and might be ‘ nobilis ’ without having either.
